Lake Molch is a large lake found just west of Great Kourend. Here, players can speak to Alry the Angler to engage in aerial fishing, a combined Fishing and Hunter activity. It requires a minimum level of 43 Fishing and 35 Hunter. Players can hunt for various fish and salamanders with a cormorant, much like falconry where players hunt kebbits with a gyr falcon.

  • 2 Hunter creatures

Getting there[edit | edit source]

To reach the island in the centre of Lake Molch, the player must take a boat at one of the three docks located on the northern, western, and eastern shores of the lake.

  • To reach the northern or eastern dock the player can use fairy ring DJR to the chasm of fire and either run south-west for the eastern dock or west for the northern dock.
  • To reach the eastern dock, the player can teleport to Shayzien using Kharedst's Memoirs and run West.
  • To reach the western dock, the player can use a Skills Necklace to teleport to the Farming Guild and run southeast through Molch

Hunter creatures[edit | edit source]

The following Hunter creatures are found in this area, which can be caught using the aerial fishing technique:

Creature Fishing Hunter Cooking
Level Exp Level Exp Level Exp
Bluegill 43 11.5 35 16.5 1 3.5
Common tench 56 40 51 45 1 10
Mottled eel 73 65 68 90 1 20
Greater siren 91 100 87 130 1 25

The following items may also be rarely obtained:

  • Golden tench: There is a 1/20,000 chance that players may receive this cosmetic equippable fish in place of a regular catch. Players who do not want it can exchange it with Alry the Angler for 100 Molch pearls.
  • Clue bottles.

Personalities[edit | edit source]

  • Alry the Angler is found on Molch Island.

Changes[edit | edit source]

Date Changes
7 February 2019
(update | poll)

The golden tench can now be exchanged for 100 Molch pearls by speaking to Alry the Angler.

31 January 2019
(update)

The rate of Molch pearls now scale based on Fishing and Hunter level. Previously they were obtained at a flat rate of 1/100. The angler's outfit was also added to the store.

Trivia[edit | edit source]

  • The examine text on the boat that transports you to Molch Island is a reference to the viral internet meme "Boaty McBoatface"

'''Lake Molch''' is a large lake found just west of [[Great Kourend]]. Here, players can speak to [[Alry the Angler]] to engage in [[aerial fishing]], a combined [[Fishing]] and [[Hunter]] activity. It requires a minimum level of 43 Fishing and 35 Hunter. Players can hunt for various fish and salamanders with a [[cormorant]], much like [[falconry]] where players hunt [[Kebbit (disambiguation)|kebbits]] with a [[gyr falcon]].

==Getting there==
To reach the island in the centre of [[Lake Molch]], the player must take a boat at one of the three docks located on the northern, western, and eastern shores of the lake.

*To reach the northern or eastern dock the player can use [[fairy ring]] {{Fairycode|DJR}} to the chasm of fire and either run south-west for the eastern dock or west for the northern dock.
*To reach the eastern dock, the player can teleport to [[Shayzien]] using Kharedst's Memoirs and run West.
*To reach the western dock, the player can use a [[Skills Necklace]] to teleport to the [[Farming Guild]] and run southeast through [[Molch]]
